Launch Two EC2 Web Servers

Step 1: Launch EC2->Amazon Linux 2->Create security group:->web-sg

Add rules:
Type	Port	Source
SSH	22	My IP
HTTP	80	0.0.0.0/0

Click:Launch Instance

Step 3: Connect to EC2
Use EC2 Instance Connect or SSH.

Run these commands:

sudo yum update -y
sudo yum install httpd -y
sudo systemctl start httpd
sudo systemctl enable httpd
echo "This is Server 1" | sudo tee /var/www/html/index.html

Step 4: Launch Second EC2 Instance
Repeat same steps.

Instance name:webserver-2
Run these commands



Create Application Load Balancer

EC2 → Security Groups → Create Security Group->Name:lb-sg

Add rule:
Type	Port	Source
HTTP	80	0.0.0.0/0

Save security group.

EC2 → Target Groups → Create Target Group
Setting	Value
Target Type	Instance
Name	web-servers-tg
Protocol	HTTP
Port	80

Health Check Path:/

Click:Next

Step 3: Register Targets

Select:
webserver-1
webserver-2

Click:Include as pending below

Then:
Create target group

EC2 → Load Balancers → Create Load Balancer
Choose:Application Load Balancer

Step 5: Configure ALB
Setting	Value
Name	my-alb
Scheme	Internet-facing
IP Type	IPv4

Listener:
HTTP : 80
Step 6: Configure Network

Choose:
Default VPC
Select at least 2 subnets


Step 7: Attach Security Group

Choose:lb-sg

Step 8: Attach Target Group
Select existing target group:web-servers-tg

Click:Create Load Balancer

Load Balancer → Copy DNS Name




Create Auto Scaling Group
EC2 → Instances->Select:webserver-1
Click:Actions → Image and templates → Create Image

Image name:my-webserver-ami
Click:Create image

EC2 → Launch Templates → Create Launch Template
Configure:
Setting	Value
Template Name	my-launch-template
AMI	my-webserver-ami
Instance Type	t2.micro
Key Pair	Your key pair
Security Group	web-sg

Click:Create Launch Template

EC2 → Auto Scaling Groups → Create Auto Scaling Group
Name:webserver-asg
Launch Template:my-launch-template
Click:Next

Step 4: Configure Network
Choose:Default VPC
Select all subnets

Step 5: Attach Load Balancer
Choose:Attach to an existing load balancer
Select:my-alb

Health Check Type:ELB

Health Check Grace Period:
300

Step 6: Configure Scaling
Setting	Value
Desired Capacity	2
Minimum Capacity	1
Maximum Capacity	4

Click:Next

Step 7: Create ASG
Review settings.

Click:Create Auto Scaling Group





PART 4 — Test Auto Scaling
EC2 → Auto Scaling Groups → Instances

You should see:2 running instances
Step 2: Test Auto Recovery
Terminate one EC2 instance manually.
ASG automatically launches another instance.
This proves:Auto Healing / Auto Recovery

